This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new RNN structure for recommendation systems. It also involves the use of attention mechanisms, which are commonly used in machine learning. 

It could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as the paper deals with recommending items to users based on their history. 

Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it involves natural language processing techniques to model user interests. 

The paper also involves the use of AI techniques to model user interests and recommend items, which could place it under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

Finally, it could be categorized under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it deals with recommending items to users based on their history and interests, which are often influenced by social networks.
